Title: Quantum Gravity, Cosmology, (Liouville) Strings and Lorentz Invariance
Authors: Nick E. Mavromatos (King's Coll. London)
Comments: 25 pages LATEX, uses special macros, invited talk at Beyond the
  Desert 2002, Oulu (Finland), June 2-7 2002 minor typos corrected, references
  added
\\
  I review some aspects of non-critical strings in connection with
Lorentz-Invariance violating approaches to quantum gravity. I also argue how
non-critical strings may provide a unifying framework where string Cosmology
and quantum gravity may be tackled together.
